    "text": "CRISPR components targeting the sorghum genome were delivered to protoplasts via polyethylene glycol-mediated transfection, both plasmid-mediated and ribonucleoprotein-based. Targeted deep sequencing analyzed frequencies of small insertions and deletions induced by sgRNAs targeting four endogenous sorghum genes.",
    "entities": [],
    "relations": []
  },
  {
    "text": "Protoplasts were isolated from sorghum leaves. Plants were cultivated under three conditions. Cultivation with seven days of a 16-h light/8-h dark photoperiod followed by three days of continuous darkness yielded the highest viable protoplasts and transfection efficiency.",
